               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380514-name-1341" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380514-name-1341" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380514-name-1341" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380514-name-1341" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MOORE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a hair-dresser. On the 30th of April the prisoner came to me, with another man, who wanted his hair cut, and while I was doing it the prisoner was very busy about the shop, looking about—the other man got up, with his hair half cut, and said, "I won't have any more of this;" and they both went out without paying me—about three minutes after they were gone I missed three razors and a hair front—these are them—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Which man went out first? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> You went out first—I asked you to sit down, but you would not—you went to the glass and combed your hair out—you have come into my shop before you washed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380514-name-1342" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380514-name-1342" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380514-name-1342" type="surname" value="HOGG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380514-name-1342" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HOGG</persName>
                  </hi>. Between five and six o'clock, in the evening of the 30th of April, I was in the tap-room of the King's Arms, and bought these two razors of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Was there not another man with me? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> There was not.</p>
